      <div class="step screensteps-section screensteps-depth-1" id="add_content" data-step-uuid="FC552DDE-BB69-4D77-B43F-CDF844FD0E50">
    <h2 id="add_content" class="step-title screensteps-heading">Add Content</h2>
        <div class="image screensteps-image">
      <img src="https://media.screensteps.com/image_assets/assets/004/500/033/original/f619f7a4-228b-4142-9ca4-0097dc50bb5a.png" srcset="" alt="Add Content" height="592" width="836">
  </div>
 
      <div class="step-instructions screensteps-textblock">
  <div id="text-content_EF3E6110-215D-0135-A08E-22000AB760A3" class="text-block-content">
    <p>Canvas already creates a rich text content box for each page. Type your content in the text box and use the toolbar to format your text. </p>
<p><strong>Notes: </strong></p>
<ul>
<li>The discussion reply Rich Content Editor includes a word count display below the bottom right corner of the text box.</li>
<li>Math equations must be added using the <a href="/t5/Instructor-Guide/How-do-I-use-the-math-Equation-Editor-in-the-Rich-Content-Editor/ta-p/816" target="_blank">Math Editor</a> in the Rich Content Editor.</li>
</ul>
  </div>
</div>
 
  </div>

